Australian GP: Sauber's Nasr &amp; Ericsson delighted with points finishes
Sauber's Felipe Nasr and Marcus Ericsson discuss their double points finish at the Australian Grand Prix.Nasr finished fifth on his Formula 1 debut, while Ericsson took 8th place and showed off some impressive overtaking manoeuvres.The team did not even take part in first practice on Friday after beingembroiled in a legal disputewith Dutch driver Giedo van der Garde.Available to UK users only.